<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/332377-was-anyone-else-bothered-by-the">Was anyone else bothered by the anachronism in &quot;Home&quot;? I mean the television news story about blacks being set on by dogs and having fire hoses turned on them. This novel is supposed to be simultaneous with &quot;Gilead&quot;, which seems to take place around 1956, but the TV news story mentioned in &quot;Home&quot; couldn&#39;t have aired before around 1963.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_332377'><a id="like_count_community_question_332377" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/332377?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">4 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F2924318-home">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/332377-was-anyone-else-bothered-by-the">7 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/332377-was-anyone-else-bothered-by-the">See all 7 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
