<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/6454366-anne-payne"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1317056865i/6454366._UX100_CR0,8,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6454366-anne-payne">Anne Payne</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I have read &quot;Gilead&quot; but not &quot;Home&quot; so I hope I&apos;m not being an uninformed gratuitous commenter. I just wanted to say that the Montgomery bus boycott t<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I have read "Gilead" but not "Home" so I hope I'm not being an uninformed gratuitous commenter. I just wanted to say that the Montgomery bus boycott took place in 1956-7, and there was definitely accompanying violence. I don't know whether this addresses the issue you raise completely.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
